  3.9786306067778397`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b63b54a2-275d-1342-9fa2-\
334399f0221c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "For mass sum rules, you can use a different symbol to represent amplitudes, \
e.g., ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ampType", " ", "->", " ", 
   RowBox[{"{", "m", "}"}]}]], "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "7ec60c8b-2e33-e44f-ac7d-c584bb6b1359"],
 ". It is also possible to add a column of your own custom labels to the \
amplitudes table using the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"labelAmps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"system", ",", " ", "colName", ",", " ", "labels"}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->"a8dfcca2-1007-1846-8c59-091de58c9b29"],
 " function (there is also an ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "unlabelAmps"], "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "c8cfca50-2910-ec4d-ac0d-b9827512dcb8"],
 " function if needed)."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9669587454157104`*^9, 3.966958813429323*^9}, {
